# CC PROMPT — v2.38.2 — CommandPanel unified scroll region

## What this does

Fixes the "panel isn't scrollable for the full height, just some sections"
report on the Commands slide-in panel (toggle icon next to sidebar) and
the Commands main tab. Browser zoom made it worse because every child
grows while the viewport stays the same.

### Root cause

`gui/src/components/CommandPanel.jsx` inner column (`<div className="flex
flex-col h-full">`) stacks ~9 siblings — task input, AgentFeed, full-output
shortcut, live trace, ChoiceBar, ClarificationWidget, TaskTemplates,
RecentTasks, tag filter bar, tool list. Only the last one (the tool
list) has `flex-1 overflow-y-auto`. Everything else has no flex-shrink
and no overflow.

Flex items default to `min-height: auto`, which means a `flex-1` child
cannot shrink below its own content's intrinsic height. The tool list
with 50+ items therefore can't shrink even when its siblings above
collectively demand more space than the panel has. When Templates and
Recent are both open the sum of the "natural-height" siblings easily
exceeds 100% of the panel; the tool list gets squeezed to near-zero or
pushed below the viewport, and nothing else scrolls because nothing
else has an overflow container.

Browser zoom compounds this: every child scales with zoom but the
viewport height doesn't, so total content overflow grows linearly with
zoom factor.

### Fix

Restructure to exactly two zones:

1. **Sticky top** (`shrink-0`, never scrolls) — task input textarea +
   Run button + agent message only.
2. **Single outer scroll region** (`flex-1 overflow-y-auto min-h-0`) —
   everything else: AgentFeed, full-output shortcut, live trace,
   ChoiceBar, ClarificationWidget, TaskTemplates, RecentTasks, tag
   filter bar, AND the tool list as plain flow.

Drop the tool list's own `flex-1 overflow-y-auto` — it becomes plain
content inside the outer scroll. Add `min-h-0` to the outer column so
the scroll region can actually shrink below content height.

Same fix applies to both `mode="panel"` (slide-in 360px) and `mode="tab"`
(main tab full-width) — they share the same `inner` variable in the
component. The existing nested scroll on the live-trace box (maxHeight:
100, overflowY: auto) is preserved as-is — it's a 100px clamp, rarely
needs to scroll, and nested scrolling of that small region is fine.

Version bump: 2.38.1 → 2.38.2 (`.x.2` — single-file UI fix, no schema,
no new deps, no new Settings).

